ril 2018 he was one of 77 applicants for the vacant [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon national team]] job.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43869356|title=77 applicants for vacant Cameroon coaching position|date=23 April 2018|accessdate=27 April 2018|author=Oluwashina Okeleji|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;A.C. Milan<ref name=\"A.C. Milan Hall of Fame: Marco Simone\"/>\n*[[Serie A]]: [[1991\u201392 Serie A|1991\u201392]], [[1992\u201393 Serie A|1992\u201393]], [[1993\u201394 Serie A|1993\u201394]], [[1995\u201396 Serie A|1995\u201396]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[1993 Supercoppa Italiana|1993]], [[1994 Supercoppa Italiana|1994]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League|European Cup and UEFA Champions League]]:<ref>From the [[1992\u201393 UEFA Champions League|1992\u201393 season]], the [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]] changed its structure and was renamed the [[UEFA Champions League]].</ref> [[1989\u201390 European Cup|1989\u201390]], [[1993\u201394 UEFA Champions League|1993\u201394]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup|European Super Cup]]: [[1989 European Super Cup|1989]], [[1994 UEFA Super Cup|1994]]\n*[[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]: [[1989 Intercontinental Cup|1989]]\n\n;Paris Saint-Germain<ref name=eurosport.com/>\n*[[Coupe de France]]: [[1997\u201398 Coupe de France|1997\u201398]]\n*[[Coupe de la Ligue]]: [[1998 Coupe de la Ligue Final|1997\u201398]]\n*[[Troph\u00e9e des Champions]]: [[1998 Troph\u00e9e des Champions|1998]]<ref>{{cite news \n|url=https://archivesparisfootball.wordpress.com/2014/07/27/lens-psg-0-1-300798-trophee-des-champions-98-99/\n|title=Lens \u2013 PSG 0-1, 30/07/98, Troph\u00e9e des Champions 98-99\n|publisher=archivesparisfootball.wordpress.com\n|accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n;A.S. Monaco<ref name=eurosport.com>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.com/football/marco-simone_prs1416/person.shtml|title=Marco Simone|publisher=Eurosport|accessdate=3 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Ligue 1|French Division 1]]: [[1999\u20132000 French Division 1|1999\u20132000]]\n*[[Troph\u00e9e des Champions]]: [[2000 Troph\u00e9e des Champions|2000]]<ref>{{cite news \n|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2000-07-22/as-monaco-fc-vs-fc-nantes/1193380/\n|title=AS Monaco FC 0:0 (6 : 5 P) FC Nantes Atlantique\n|publisher=globalsportsarchive.com\n|accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Individual===\n*Serie C1 top-scorer: 1987\u201388 (15 goals)<ref name=magliarossonera.it/>\n*[[Troph\u00e9es UNFP du football#Player of the Year|Ligue 1 Player of the Year]]: 1998<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sportpalmares.eu/Trophees-UNFP-Oscars-du-football.html |title= Palmar\u00e8s Troph\u00e9es UNFP - Oscars du football - Meilleur joueur de Ligue 1 |publisher=www.sportpalmares.eu |language=fr |accessdate=2 August 2017 }}</ref>\n*''[[France Football]]'' 's Best Foreign Player in France: [[1997\u201398 French Division 1|1997\u201398]], 1999\u20132000<ref name=magliarossonera.it/><ref name=\"gq\">{{cite web |url=https://www.gqitalia.it/sport/calcio/2018/07/09/calciomercato-i-10-migliori-calciatori-italiani-in-francia |title=Calciomercato, i 10 migliori calciatori italiani in Francia |publisher=GQ Italia |language=Italian |last1=Stabile |first1=Adriano |date=9 July 2018 |accessdate=23 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"francefootball\">{{cite web |url=https://www.francefootball.fr/fiche/joueur/simone-marco-ita/2943 |title=Marco Simone |publisher=France Football |language=French |accessdate=23 March 2020 }}</ref>\n*A.C. Milan Hall of Fame<ref name=\"A.C. Milan Hall of Fame: Marco Simone\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Lequipe|2943}}\n*{{TuttoCalciatori|Simone_Marco}}\n*[http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=27&squadra=2 Profile at FIGC.it] {{in lang|it}} {{dead link|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-sports}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ra\u00ed]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] captain|years=1